    "description": "Pymdu (Urban Data Model) is a Python package designed to collect, post-process, model, and analyze urban data. It draws inspiration from and reuses tools like GeoClimate, UWG, UMEP-DEV, t4gpd, and pythermalcomfort to offer a complete solution for urban environmental analysis. A key application of pymdu is outdoor thermal comfort analysis, enabling the simulation and optimization of urban spaces to improve the well-being of residents.",
